From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Buildroot <buildroot@buildroot.org>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 02:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] spl: fit: try bitstream loader for FPGA images

Vivado .bit files include a header before the raw FPGA configuration
payload. The regular fpga_load() path expects the payload to start at the
bitstream sync data, so using it directly from SPL FIT leaves the image in
DDR but does not program the PL.

Match the non-SPL FIT boot path by trying fpga_loadbitstream() first. If
that fails, fall back to fpga_load() so existing FIT images containing a
raw/bin payload continue to work.

Signed-off-by: Buildroot <buildroot@buildroot.org>
---
 common/spl/spl_fit.c | 7 ++++++-
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/common/spl/spl_fit.c b/common/spl/spl_fit.c
--- a/common/spl/spl_fit.c
+++ b/common/spl/spl_fit.c
@@ -615,8 +615,15 @@ static int spl_fit_upload_fpga(struct spl_fit_info *ctx, int node,
 			      compatible);
 	}
 
-	ret = fpga_load(devnum, (void *)fpga_image->load_addr,
-			fpga_image->size, BIT_FULL, flags);
+	/*
+	 * Vivado .bit files carry a header. Try the bitstream-aware loader
+	 * first, then keep supporting FIT images that embed raw/bin payloads.
+	 */
+	ret = fpga_loadbitstream(devnum, (void *)fpga_image->load_addr,
+				 fpga_image->size, BIT_FULL);
+	if (ret)
+		ret = fpga_load(devnum, (void *)fpga_image->load_addr,
+				fpga_image->size, BIT_FULL, flags);
 	if (ret) {
 		printf("%s: Cannot load the image to the FPGA\n", __func__);
 		return ret;
-- 
